  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package conforms to the Minimal profile and carries a SHA-256 integrity hash but no digital signature, making structural integrity unverifiable (W-SI-01). All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven factors show achieved levels below required levels. Decision outcome is Accepted for synthetic adversarial testing purposes.",
